Question 2: Difference between Abstract Class and Interface?

Abstract Class	Interface

Can have implementation	Only method declaration
Supports constructors	No constructor
Supports fields	No fields
Single inheritance	Multiple interfaces possible


Example:

public interface ILogger
{
    void Log(string message);
}


---

Question 3: What is Dependency Injection?

Answer

Dependency Injection is a design pattern where dependencies are injected into a class instead of creating them inside the class.

Example:

public class OrderService
{
    private readonly ILogger _logger;

    public OrderService(ILogger logger)
    {
        _logger = logger;
    }
}

Benefits:

Loose coupling

Easy unit testing

Better maintainability



