4. SQL Questions (5 min)

Question 10: Difference between INNER JOIN and LEFT JOIN

INNER JOIN

Returns only matching records.

SELECT *
FROM Orders o
INNER JOIN Customers c
ON o.CustomerId = c.Id

LEFT JOIN

Returns all records from left table.

SELECT *
FROM Customers c
LEFT JOIN Orders o
ON c.Id = o.CustomerId


---

Question 11: What is Index?

Index improves query performance.

CREATE INDEX idx_customer_name
ON Customers(Name);


---

Question 12: Difference between DELETE and TRUNCATE

DELETE	TRUNCATE

Removes rows with condition	Removes all rows
Can rollback	Cannot rollback
Slower	Faster



