1. What happens internally when a Web API request comes in?

Expected Answer (Good Candidate)

Flow should include:

1. Request comes to Kestrel Server


2. Goes through Middleware Pipeline


3. Routing identifies Controller


4. Model Binding


5. Filters executed


6. Controller Action executes


7. Response returned



Example pipeline:

Client Request
      ↓
Kestrel Server
      ↓
Middleware (Auth, Logging, etc)
      ↓
Routing
      ↓
Controller
      ↓
Action Method
      ↓
Response

Red Flag

Candidate says only:

> "Controller handles request"




