2. What is the difference between IEnumerable and IQueryable?

Correct Answer

IEnumerable	IQueryable

Works in memory	Works with database
LINQ to Objects	LINQ to Entities
Executes in application	Executes in database
Poor for large datasets	Better performance


Example:

var users = context.Users.Where(x => x.Age > 25);

With IQueryable → SQL executed in DB.


