7. What is the difference between Add, AddAsync, and SaveChanges in EF Core?

Expected Answer

context.Users.Add(user);
context.SaveChanges();

Explanation:

Add() → Adds entity to tracking

AddAsync() → Async version

SaveChanges() → Executes SQL INSERT


Important concept:

> SQL is executed only during SaveChanges.




